The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, May 31, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, May 31, 2003				 																																	What to do this weekend				 																																	Attend The Telegraph Merchants Cup Football 2003 at CC amp;FC, presented by Haywards 5000, 4.30 pm.				 																Dance				 																																	Take the kids to On Toes, a dance workshop, for seven to 16-year-olds, at Oxford Bookstore. On Saturday from 4.30 pm and from 3.30 pm onSunday.				 																Exhibitions				 																																	Enjoy an exhibition of pottery at the Central Cottage Industries Emporium, from 10 am to 2 pm.				 																																	Admire paintings and Ikebana by Bageshree Dutta and Arundhati Sarkar, at the Academy of Fine Arts, New South Gallery, from 3 pm to 8 pm				 																																	Take a look at Parallel Stream, an exhibition by artists of India, Bangladesh, Korea and Bulgaria, at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3 pm to 8 pm				 																Energy				 																																	Spare a thought for the environment at a seminar and exhibition, Energy for the Future, organised by the Indian Institute of Chemical Engineers. From 10 am on Saturday and 11 am on Sunday at Taj Bengal.
